==English==
===Pronunciation===
*yô, /jɔː/, /jO:/
*:'''Homophones''' (''non-rhotic accents''): [[yore]], [[your]], [[you're]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɔː|Rhymes: -ɔː]]

===Verb===
'''to yaw''' ([[yaws]], [[yawed]], [[yawing]])
# (''of an aircraft etc'') to [[turn]] about the [[vertical]] [[axis]] while maintaining [[course]]
# {{nautical}} to [[swerve]] off course to [[port]] or [[starboard]].

===Noun===
'''yaw'''
# an act of yawing
# the [[extent]] of yawing
# {{nautical}} A characteristic of unsteadiness, twitchy to [[helm]], requiring much attention to maintain course, said of a ship or boat.

